SIMPLE: azo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Azo-
<hw>Az"o-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[See <er>Azote</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining form of <xex>azote</xex></def>;
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Applied loosely to compounds having nitrogen variously
combined, as in cyanides, nitrates, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Now
especially applied to compounds containing a two atom nitrogen group
uniting two hydrocarbon radicals, as in <xex>azo</xex>benzene,
<xex>azo</xex>benzoic, etc. These compounds furnish many artificial
dyes. See <er>Diazo-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Azobenzene</ent>⟦br⟧
